<h2>How to reach Meghalaya / Meghalaya Tour Guide</h2>

<p><strong>By Air</strong>- To get into Meghaalay via flights, you need to reach Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport in Guwahati, which is the nearest airport to Meghalaya.</p>

<p><strong>By Road</strong>- Meghalaya state is well-connected to many other states via national highway. You can easily visit Meghalaya via road; however, being a hilly area, hiring an experienced driver is advisable.</p>

<p><strong>By Train</strong>- Guwahati Railway Station is the closest railway station to Meghalaya. You can reach Guwahati station and then take public transport to reach your desired place.</p>

<h2>Best Places to Visit in Meghalaya ? Top Tourist Places in Meghalaya</h2>

<h3>Shillong</h3>
<p>Shillong, one of the top tourist places in Meghalaya, attracts many visitors every year. The capital city is famous for its scenic beauty and rich heritage. Book Meghalaya tour packages with us.</p>

<h3>Cherrapunji</h3>
<p>A small city, that holds natural beauty, waterfalls, and living root bridge, the Double Decker Living Root Bridge, Nohkalikai Falls, Mawsmai Cave, and the Seven Sisters Falls are some of the popular places in Meghalaya.</p>

<h3>Dawki</h3>
<p>Dawki, one of the best places to visit in Meghalaya, is famous for the Umngot River.You can enjoy boat rides and kayaking at Dawki with our Meghalaya tour packages.</p>

<h3>Mawlynnong</h3>
<p>Take a tour of the cleanest village in Asia, Mamlynnong. Immerse yourself in the traditional lifestyle and culture of this little hamlet with our Meghalaya travel packages.</p>

<h3>Nongriat</h3>
<p>A small village that reflects unreal mountain beauty at every corner, makes visitors mesmerized with its scenic beauty, living root bridge, and pleasant surroundings. Book Meghalaya holiday packages with invisit to witness the spellbound beauty of Meghalaya.</p>

<h3>Nongkhnum Island</h3>
<p>Take a tour of Asia&rsquo;s largest river island and immerse yourself in its splendid beauty. While on a trip to Meghalaya, don&rsquo;t miss out on adding Nongkhnum Island to your itinerary.</p>

<h3>Jowai</h3>
<p>Jowai, a beautiful, small hillock, is one the best places to visit in Meghalaya. This popular hill station is nothing but filled with pure natural beauty. Get our Meghaalaya tour packages to explore Joowai in Meghalaya.</p>

<h2>Top Things to do in Meghalaya / Best Activities in Meghalaya</h2>

<h3>Water sports at Umiam Lake</h3>
<p>Immerse yourself in the various water sports at the most beautiful lake in Meghalaya, Umiam lake. You can go boating, kayaking, and angling with your family and friends.</p>

<h3>Trek in Meghalaya</h3>
<p>As Meghalaya is home to the green mountains, this allows visitors to trek and explore the charming mountains. David Scott Trail, Umden Village Trek, The Living Roots Bridge Trek, and Mawlongbna Village Trekking are some of the popular treks in Meghalaya.</p>

<h3>Shopping at Police Bazar</h3>
<p>While on a trip to Meghalaya, don&rsquo;t forget to visit Police Bazar to shop for local handicraft products. Book Meghalaya tour packages to explore all the top things to do in Meghalaya.</p>

<h3>Visit Lady Hydari Park</h3>
<p>A beautiful park that has been named after the former governor of Assam is one of the top things to do in Meghalaya. It has a butterfly garden that is full of various rare flowers and well-maintained lawns.</p>

<h3>Jadoh food</h3>
<p>Don&rsquo;t forget to add Jadoh, the famous street food of Meghalaya, to your Meghalaya itinerary. This one is the most popular street food in Meghalaya.</p>

<h3>Hot Springs in Jakrem</h3>
<p>Taking bath at Jakrem hot spring is one of the top things to do in Meghalaya. Book Meghalaya tour packages with invisit to explore every corner of Meghalaya.</p>

<h3>Elephant Falls</h3>
<p>A milky white waterfall coming from a large Elephant shaped rock, is one of the top things to do in Meghalaya. Book Meghalaya holiday packages to experience the best activities to do in Meghalaya.</p>

